00:15:20,247 --> 00:15:21,014
What else?

285
00:15:21,611 --> 00:15:22,180
Uh…

286
00:15:23,031 --> 00:15:25,306
I must separate colored clothes from whites
before sending them to the laundry

287
00:15:25,739 --> 00:15:27,411
and I must wash my underwear myself.

288
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:28,777
My son is the best.

289
00:15:28,998 --> 00:15:29,699
Let’s hug.

290
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,154
I love you, Mom.

291
00:15:32,364 --> 00:15:33,054
I know.

292
00:15:37,048 --> 00:15:37,773
Stop it.

293
00:15:38,235 --> 00:15:40,235
- You’re giving me goosebumps.
- I love you too, Kloy.

294
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:41,186
I know you love me.

295
00:15:41,214 --> 00:15:41,749
You don’t have to do this.

296
00:15:41,765 --> 00:15:43,749
Mom, I love you too.

297
00:15:44,066 --> 00:15:44,721
What are you doing?

298
00:15:44,829 --> 00:15:46,038
She’s my mom.

299
00:15:46,511 --> 00:15:47,411
You’re my friend.

300
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:48,968
My friend’s mom is like my own.

301
00:15:49,044 --> 00:15:49,377
Mom.

302
00:15:49,395 --> 00:15:49,878
Hey.

303
00:15:50,376 --> 00:15:51,878
Stop it.

304
00:15:51,903 --> 00:15:52,800
Stop it.

305
00:15:53,145 --> 00:15:53,706
Hey.

306
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,745
Don’t do that to your friend.

307
00:15:58,211 --> 00:16:01,398
Welcome back to our heaven, Mr. Yotha.

308
00:16:02,758 --> 00:16:03,629
Did you buy all of this yourself?

309
00:16:03,765 --> 00:16:05,020
Yes, of course.

310
00:16:05,515 --> 00:16:07,882
I can’t have my beloved big bro
be uncomfortable, can I?

311
00:16:08,170 --> 00:16:09,567
Is it you or me who fears being uncomfortable?

312
00:16:09,847 --> 00:16:11,120
Sit down.

313
00:16:11,525 --> 00:16:12,976
Come on. I’m hungry.

314
00:16:13,204 --> 00:16:13,909
Let’s go find something to eat.

315
00:16:14,152 --> 00:16:15,140
Won’t it be easier to just order food delivery?

316
00:16:16,321 --> 00:16:16,822
Sure.

317
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:17,628
What do you want to eat?

318
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:18,937
Up to you.

319
00:16:19,543 --> 00:16:21,217
Japanese food, then.

320
00:16:21,407 --> 00:16:21,920
Is that okay?

321
00:16:23,057 --> 00:16:23,521
Yeah.

322
00:16:23,589 --> 00:16:25,562
Okay, I’ll place the order now,

323
00:16:25,582 --> 00:16:26,314
but you’ll pay.

324
00:16:27,585 --> 00:16:28,238
You’ll pay.

325
00:16:29,611 --> 00:16:30,518
I’m your little brother

326
00:16:30,998 --> 00:16:33,000
and you want me to pay?

327
00:16:33,077 --> 00:16:33,654
Let’s split the bill.

328
00:16:34,210 --> 00:16:36,174
Fine, we can do that.

329
00:16:46,668 --> 00:16:49,097
Freedom smells sweet.

330
00:16:49,829 --> 00:16:52,677
I really want to take a photo of your face
right now and send it to your mom.

331
00:16:53,644 --> 00:16:55,884
I’m still her good son.

332
00:16:55,971 --> 00:16:56,361
Sure.

333
00:16:56,377 --> 00:16:57,524
Don’t even think about telling on me.

334
00:16:58,414 --> 00:16:58,911
Hey,

335
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:01,592
I’ve been meaning to ask you something.

336
00:17:02,085 --> 00:17:02,600
What is it?

337
00:17:03,188 --> 00:17:06,506
Well, why do you sleep with the lights on?

338
00:17:07,069 --> 00:17:08,262
Haven’t you ever slept with the lights on?

339
00:17:09,014 --> 00:17:09,700
I have,

340
00:17:10,281 --> 00:17:12,398
but only when I’m somewhere unfamiliar.

341
00:17:14,151 --> 00:17:15,124
Do you leave the lights on every night?

342
00:17:16,084 --> 00:17:16,616
Yeah,

343
00:17:17,303 --> 00:17:19,161
but if you can’t sleep, you can tell me.

344
00:17:19,617 --> 00:17:20,362
Don’t hold back.

345
00:17:20,638 --> 00:17:21,613
No.

346
00:17:22,026 --> 00:17:22,936
I’ll be fine.

347
00:17:22,961 --> 00:17:23,945
No problem.

348
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:26,490
I just want to know...

349
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,272
if you’ve been sleeping with
the lights on since you were born.

350
00:17:30,306 --> 00:17:30,828
No.

351
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,823
I think it started when I was about 5 or 6 years old.

352
00:17:33,361 --> 00:17:35,456
I was stuck in the storage room for like an hour,

353
00:17:35,970 --> 00:17:36,921
and then I became traumatized.

354
00:17:37,328 --> 00:17:37,859
Oh.

355
00:17:37,878 --> 00:17:39,374
Since then, my mind's been wondering.

356
00:17:39,454 --> 00:17:40,208
You mean wandering.

357
00:17:40,296 --> 00:17:40,903
Heh.

358
00:17:42,472 --> 00:17:45,468
Yeah, I started thinking that in the dark,

359
00:17:45,539 --> 00:17:47,903
there are ghosts or something scary.

360
00:17:48,174 --> 00:17:48,897
Ah.

361
00:17:49,229 --> 00:17:50,202
I just don’t like

362
00:17:50,386 --> 00:17:52,269
not being able to see what’s around me.

363
00:17:52,453 --> 00:17:52,973
That’s all.

364
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:54,336
We’ve studied together since secondary school.

365
00:17:54,611 --> 00:17:56,149
Why did you never tell me about this?

366
00:17:56,309 --> 00:17:58,096
It’s not important

367
00:17:58,586 --> 00:18:00,731
and I didn’t think I’d become your roommate.

368
00:18:01,468 --> 00:18:02,265
That’s true.

369
00:18:02,909 --> 00:18:05,164
But what if the power goes out?

370
00:18:05,423 --> 00:18:06,306
Will you need any medicine?

371
00:18:06,398 --> 00:18:07,281
Where’s your medicine?

372
00:18:07,299 --> 00:18:07,874
Tell me.

373
00:18:07,891 --> 00:18:08,933
It’s not that bad.

374
00:18:09,656 --> 00:18:10,974
It’s just that if I sleep in the dark,

375
00:18:11,531 --> 00:18:12,900
I’ll have a nightmare.

376
00:18:13,308 --> 00:18:15,900
I won’t have trouble breathing
or go into shock like you think.

377
00:18:16,451 --> 00:18:18,106
Alright, that’s a relief.

378
00:18:20,749 --> 00:18:21,269
I’m hungry.

379
00:18:21,545 --> 00:18:22,202
Have you eaten?

380
00:18:22,631 --> 00:18:23,121
Not yet.

381
00:18:23,710 --> 00:18:24,697
Shall we go get something to eat downstairs?

382
00:18:25,069 --> 00:18:25,663
Let’s go, buddy.

383
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,158
Yes.

384
00:18:26,705 --> 00:18:27,216
Let’s go.

385
00:18:27,767 --> 00:18:28,780
I’m hungry.

386
00:18:31,339 --> 00:18:32,108
What should we eat?

387
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:36,980
Is that Japanese food?

388
00:18:38,699 --> 00:18:39,211
Yes.

389
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:40,617
Japanese food looks good.

390
00:18:45,685 --> 00:18:46,477
Let’s eat.

391
00:18:46,802 --> 00:18:47,718
Let’s get some Japanese food.

392
00:18:48,684 --> 00:18:49,311
Japanese food.

393
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:50,259
Let’s go!

394
00:18:53,091 --> 00:18:54,299
All the food looks so good.

395
00:18:56,398 --> 00:18:56,897
Shall we?

396
00:18:57,263 --> 00:18:57,746
Let’s go.

397
00:19:05,346 --> 00:19:06,060
So good.

398
00:19:06,152 --> 00:19:07,097
This one is good too.

399
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:08,776
Oh, oh.

400
00:19:11,902 --> 00:19:12,761
Everything is delicious.

401
00:19:14,635 --> 00:19:17,173
I think we’ll spend all our money in one week.

402
00:19:19,065 --> 00:19:19,628
It’s okay.

403
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:22,524
We can ask for more.

404
00:19:22,841 --> 00:19:23,463
Yay!

405
00:19:23,838 --> 00:19:24,374
Let’s keep eating.

406
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:26,877
Where do you think I should put this, Po?

407
00:19:27,002 --> 00:19:28,032
Why don’t you put it on your head?

408
00:19:28,383 --> 00:19:29,576
Here I come.

409
00:19:29,645 --> 00:19:30,373
Do you need help with anything?

410
00:19:30,552 --> 00:19:32,450
What took you so long?

411
00:19:33,340 --> 00:19:34,838
We’re almost done.

412
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,580
Then I’m leaving.

413
00:19:37,550 --> 00:19:38,183
Just kidding.

414
00:19:42,573 --> 00:19:43,514
What’s wrong, Pun?

415
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:45,413
It’s because of you, Arm.

416
00:19:45,730 --> 00:19:46,250
Me?

417
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:47,056
Yeah.

418
00:19:47,899 --> 00:19:48,608
What did I do?

419
00:19:48,626 --> 00:19:50,807
Did I step on your feet?

420
00:19:51,053 --> 00:19:51,797
No.

421
00:19:53,112 --> 00:19:54,527
You’re here with your boyfriend.

422
00:19:54,871 --> 00:19:56,016
It makes me miss Jet.

423
00:19:56,671 --> 00:19:57,238
Come on.

424
00:19:57,644 --> 00:19:59,103
Jet went to work, not to war.

425
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,737
He’s coming to pick you up, right?

426
00:20:01,117 --> 00:20:03,177
That’s still several hours away, Arc.

427
00:20:03,893 --> 00:20:05,288
It’s alright, Pun.

428
00:20:05,859 --> 00:20:06,674
Look, Arm.

429
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:09,373
Once Arc graduates and starts working,

430
00:20:10,161 --> 00:20:11,275
you’ll know how I feel.

431
00:20:19,773 --> 00:20:21,004
We ate too much.

432
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:21,971
What should we eat next time?

433
00:20:22,497 --> 00:20:23,974
You’re already thinking about
what to eat? I’m still full.

434
00:20:24,084 --> 00:20:25,097
Crispy pork with basil would be nice though.

435
00:20:26,684 --> 00:20:27,174
Let’s go in.

436
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:32,754
I can’t unlock it.

437
00:20:33,022 --> 00:20:33,607
Let me try.

438
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:36,706
Why can’t we unlock it?

439
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:39,777
Yes?

440
00:20:40,859 --> 00:20:41,807
Can I help you?

441
00:20:42,312 --> 00:20:43,065
Who is it?

442
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:44,666
Which room is this?

443
00:20:44,764 --> 00:20:45,536
411.

444
00:20:47,054 --> 00:20:47,854
Oh, shit.

445
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:49,445
It’s the wrong floor.

446
00:20:49,468 --> 00:20:50,361
We’re sorry.

447
00:20:50,542 --> 00:20:51,570
It’s fine.

448
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,198
It’s...

449
00:20:56,437 --> 00:20:57,026
It’s fine.

450
00:21:00,951 --> 00:21:02,645
I thought they were running in.

451
00:21:03,192 --> 00:21:04,600
Luckily, I learned Taekwondo.

452
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,090
PUT THE WIDER SIDE ON TOP
OF THE NARROWER SIDE.

453
00:21:13,182 --> 00:21:14,305
This is so damn hard.

454
00:21:14,742 --> 00:21:15,798
Why do we have to tie it?

455
00:21:17,765 --> 00:21:18,602
We don’t.

456
00:21:19,217 --> 00:21:19,899
We do.

457
00:21:20,866 --> 00:21:22,420
Freshmen need to wear the uniform properly.

458
00:21:24,838 --> 00:21:25,487
Nonsense.

459
00:21:25,835 --> 00:21:26,317
Yes!

460
00:21:28,197 --> 00:21:28,721
Come here.

461
00:21:29,282 --> 00:21:29,829
Get up.

462
00:21:30,143 --> 00:21:30,684
No.

463
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:31,791
Let me tie it for you. Come on.

464
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:36,617
Here.

465
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,471
Here, look.

466
00:21:39,647 --> 00:21:41,121
So you can do it yourself next time, okay?

467
00:21:42,757 --> 00:21:43,954
You’re not looking, you jerk.

468
00:21:44,130 --> 00:21:45,573
I won’t be able to do it anyway.

469
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:46,574
Why should I look?

470
00:21:48,482 --> 00:21:49,002
Fine.

471
00:21:49,648 --> 00:21:50,724
I’ve already ordered the pre-tied ones.

472
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:51,810
They’ll arrive in a few days.

473
00:21:51,992 --> 00:21:52,568
Smart.

474
00:21:55,671 --> 00:21:56,142
Hey.

475
00:21:57,154 --> 00:21:58,025
Can I borrow your perfume?

476
00:21:58,743 --> 00:21:59,226
Yeah.

477
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:05,290
ALARM

478
00:22:51,779 --> 00:22:52,868
Hey, you cheeky kid.

479
00:22:53,091 --> 00:22:53,564
Oh.

480
00:22:55,456 --> 00:22:56,423
You’re still here.

481
00:22:57,610 --> 00:22:59,355
Do you trick me into kissing you every morning?

482
00:23:26,777 --> 00:23:27,309
Hey.

483
00:23:27,835 --> 00:23:28,327
Hmm?

484
00:23:29,005 --> 00:23:29,722
Do I look handsome yet?

485
00:23:31,496 --> 00:23:32,000
Yeah.

486
00:23:32,654 --> 00:23:33,376
Your outfit looks good

487
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:35,386
but your face looks like shit.

488
00:23:36,065 --> 00:23:36,943
Come on.

489
00:23:37,152 --> 00:23:37,974
I’ll tell Kloy about this.

490
00:23:39,235 --> 00:23:39,801
Calm down.

491
00:23:41,308 --> 00:23:42,324
Let’s talk nicely.

492
00:23:43,568 --> 00:23:45,071
We’re good friends.

493
00:23:45,413 --> 00:23:46,232
Please.

494
00:23:46,505 --> 00:23:47,579
You never shave your mustache, do you?

495
00:23:49,524 --> 00:23:50,573
What do we have to do today?

496
00:23:50,604 --> 00:23:52,177
I saw so many activities in the group chat.

497
00:23:53,552 --> 00:23:54,657
Drawing lots to get in our peer mentoring group.

498
00:23:55,032 --> 00:23:57,042
Getting our ID photos taken.

499
00:23:58,017 --> 00:23:58,640
That’s all I remember.

500
00:23:59,983 --> 00:24:02,614
I think we need to make friends.

501
00:24:02,854 --> 00:24:04,198
The two of us can’t make it on our own.

502
00:24:05,081 --> 00:24:05,562
Agreed.

503
00:24:06,391 --> 00:24:07,597
- Come on. We don’t want to be late.
- Let’s go.

504
00:24:08,922 --> 00:24:09,423
Wait.

505
00:24:11,238 --> 00:24:12,604
We’re getting our ID photos taken today, right?

506
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:13,102
Yeah.

507
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,117
Give me a moment to style my hair.

508
00:24:18,251 --> 00:24:19,114
Come on. Let me style yours.

509
00:24:19,287 --> 00:24:19,943
No.

510
00:24:20,013 --> 00:24:20,491
Don’t.

511
00:24:20,512 --> 00:24:21,706
- Do you want my help?
- No.

512
00:24:23,035 --> 00:24:24,152
Come on. Let me help you.

513
00:24:24,170 --> 00:24:25,125
Hey. Let me.

514
00:24:30,197 --> 00:24:30,909
Do I look okay?

515
00:24:31,432 --> 00:24:32,253
Yes, what about me?

516
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:34,607
Just need to fix this here.

517
00:24:36,269 --> 00:24:37,271
Come on. Let me style your hair in return.

518
00:24:37,290 --> 00:24:38,442
No need.

519
00:24:42,770 --> 00:24:43,521
Damn.

520
00:24:45,847 --> 00:24:46,888
Where do we start?

521
00:24:47,877 --> 00:24:48,594
No idea.

522
00:24:52,814 --> 00:24:53,431
Over there?

523
00:24:54,610 --> 00:24:55,202
I guess.

524
00:24:55,805 --> 00:24:56,597
Hey.

525
00:24:57,102 --> 00:24:58,807
Please grab the application

526
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:00,142
and get in the queue for the photos.

527
00:25:00,634 --> 00:25:01,973
Oh.

528
00:25:07,281 --> 00:25:08,125
My name is Faifa.

529
00:25:08,442 --> 00:25:09,161
I’m in Electrical Engineering.

530
00:25:09,548 --> 00:25:10,522
Oh.

531
00:25:10,857 --> 00:25:11,474
I’m Gun.

532
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:12,379
He’s Kong.

533
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,383
We’re in Chemical Engineering.

534
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:15,274
Oh.

535
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:17,084
I thought you were in Electrical Engineering.

536
00:25:17,114 --> 00:25:17,801
Sorry, my bad.

537
00:25:17,816 --> 00:25:18,444
Wait.

538
00:25:19,774 --> 00:25:21,336
Freshmen study together.

539
00:25:21,478 --> 00:25:23,537
We can stay together.

540
00:25:24,336 --> 00:25:24,875
You’re right.

541
00:25:25,466 --> 00:25:28,069
Let’s fill in our applications, new friends.

542
00:25:28,182 --> 00:25:28,607
Let’s go.

543
00:25:34,936 --> 00:25:36,120
Why are there so many things?

544
00:25:36,577 --> 00:25:38,002
I filled out a lot when I applied to study here.

545
00:25:38,198 --> 00:25:38,677
Right?

546
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:41,026
I gave them so much info about me,
they could turn it into a movie by now.

547
00:25:41,094 --> 00:25:41,629
Yeah.

548
00:25:44,044 --> 00:25:44,776
Oh, sorry.

549
00:25:46,062 --> 00:25:46,908
You’re lefthanded?

550
00:25:48,035 --> 00:25:48,505
Yes.

551
00:25:50,386 --> 00:25:52,598
Why are you in Chemical Engineering?

552
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:54,419
Because I could get in with my scores.

553
00:25:56,050 --> 00:25:56,648
What about you?

554
00:25:57,499 --> 00:26:00,625
Don’t tell me you’re in the Electrical department
because your name Faifa means electricity.

555
00:26:00,791 --> 00:26:01,351
Yeah.

556
00:26:02,302 --> 00:26:02,979
Are you crazy?

557
00:26:03,482 --> 00:26:04,700
If we choose based on our names,

558
00:26:05,081 --> 00:26:06,471
Kong should be studying photography.

559
00:26:06,685 --> 00:26:07,197
Oh?

560
00:26:07,973 --> 00:26:08,568
That makes sense.

561
00:26:08,887 --> 00:26:09,688
What does this have to do with me?

562
00:26:09,715 --> 00:26:10,820
Why aren’t you in Communication Arts?

563
00:26:11,653 --> 00:26:12,054
I’m done.

564
00:26:12,072 --> 00:26:12,946
That’s a totally different field.

565
00:26:12,973 --> 00:26:13,868
I’ll go get my photo taken.

566
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:14,912
Wait for me when you’re done.

567
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:15,902
Okay.

568
00:26:15,961 --> 00:26:16,565
I’ll be right back.

