00:37:52,379 --> 00:37:52,973
I won’t.

848
00:38:01,177 --> 00:38:01,936
Yotha, right?

849
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:04,468
Welcome to Perfect 10 Liners.

850
00:38:06,266 --> 00:38:07,450
Perfect 10 Liners?

851
00:38:07,645 --> 00:38:08,219
Here.

852
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:10,853
Take this too.

853
00:38:12,370 --> 00:38:15,011
And this is your gift.

854
00:38:17,745 --> 00:38:18,472
You must be confused.

855
00:38:19,022 --> 00:38:20,485
I was too when I joined.

856
00:38:20,866 --> 00:38:22,703
I’ll explain later.

857
00:38:23,709 --> 00:38:25,511
- Okay.
- Let’s make some noise for them!

858
00:38:31,041 --> 00:38:32,628
Both the senior and the junior are amazing.

859
00:38:33,045 --> 00:38:34,404
I want to take them home.

860
00:38:34,518 --> 00:38:35,017
Calm down.

861
00:38:36,954 --> 00:38:38,755
That’s Yotha.

862
00:38:42,666 --> 00:38:43,765
Does he seem as mysterious as you thought?

863
00:38:59,397 --> 00:39:00,311
Stop staring.

864
00:39:00,829 --> 00:39:03,466
When you meet him, don’t stare at his face like that.

865
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,148
He doesn’t like anyone staring at his face.

866
00:39:05,734 --> 00:39:06,555
What happens if I stare?

867
00:39:06,728 --> 00:39:07,740
He’ll beat you up.

868
00:39:08,517 --> 00:39:09,303
Beat me up?

869
00:39:10,177 --> 00:39:10,859
Just kidding

870
00:39:13,816 --> 00:39:16,057
When the activities end, can we leave right away?

871
00:39:16,613 --> 00:39:17,537
I think we can

872
00:39:17,724 --> 00:39:18,613
but I’ll leave later,

873
00:39:18,709 --> 00:39:19,711
My peer mentor asked me to eat with him.

874
00:39:20,488 --> 00:39:21,232
Then I’ll leave right away.

875
00:39:21,622 --> 00:39:22,299
My peer mentor already left.

876
00:39:22,318 --> 00:39:22,724
Okay.

877
00:39:22,743 --> 00:39:23,309
Hey.

878
00:39:24,708 --> 00:39:26,666
Looks like we both got ditched by our peer mentors.

879
00:39:27,037 --> 00:39:27,826
But it’s okay.

880
00:39:28,192 --> 00:39:29,905
I’ll take care of you.

881
00:39:30,527 --> 00:39:31,010
Huh?

882
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:33,010
I don’t want to eat alone.

883
00:39:34,665 --> 00:39:35,570
What about your peer mentor?

884
00:39:36,429 --> 00:39:38,222
My peer mentor is going with the others.

885
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:40,472
It’s only you and me left.

886
00:39:47,282 --> 00:39:47,857
Yotha.

887
00:39:48,558 --> 00:39:49,102
Yotha.

888
00:39:49,811 --> 00:39:50,315
Yes?

889
00:39:51,170 --> 00:39:52,940
Do you have a nickname?

890
00:39:52,958 --> 00:39:54,475
Or is Yotha also your nickname?

891
00:39:56,742 --> 00:39:57,616
It’s my nickname.

892
00:39:59,405 --> 00:40:00,500
That’s so cool, right, Arc?

893
00:40:01,194 --> 00:40:03,401
So your name is Yotha.
Are you in Civil Engineering?

894
00:40:04,491 --> 00:40:04,968
Yes.

895
00:40:04,988 --> 00:40:05,638
Great.

896
00:40:05,765 --> 00:40:07,201
Arc is in Civil Engineering too.

897
00:40:07,331 --> 00:40:09,072
He can help you with anything.

898
00:40:09,505 --> 00:40:11,530
Don’t forget to give him your lecture notes.

899
00:40:11,940 --> 00:40:13,281
They’re all with you.

900
00:40:15,191 --> 00:40:16,413
Why do you have to ruin it?

901
00:40:19,185 --> 00:40:20,411
Hey, Yotha.

902
00:40:20,671 --> 00:40:21,874
You have a younger brother, right?

903
00:40:22,189 --> 00:40:24,068
Yes, his name is Faifa.

904
00:40:25,459 --> 00:40:26,268
He’s in the same year.

905
00:40:28,905 --> 00:40:32,807
Don’t tell me he’s in Electrical Engineering
like his name suggests.

906
00:40:34,696 --> 00:40:36,204
That’s cool.

907
00:40:37,290 --> 00:40:40,315
Wow, your parents have planned this
since before you guys were born, huh?

908
00:40:43,425 --> 00:40:44,413
Hey, Yotha.

909
00:40:45,682 --> 00:40:46,268
Hi, guys.

910
00:40:46,671 --> 00:40:47,174
Hi.

911
00:40:47,576 --> 00:40:48,579
Hi.

912
00:40:49,136 --> 00:40:49,887
I’m Faifa,

913
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:51,490
Yotha’s younger brother.

914
00:40:51,790 --> 00:40:54,091
This is my friend Gun.

915
00:40:54,912 --> 00:40:57,182
Did your peer mentors bring you kids here too?

916
00:40:58,447 --> 00:40:59,804
How dare you call them kids.

917
00:41:00,145 --> 00:41:02,499
You’re the most childish one at this table, Arm.

918
00:41:04,117 --> 00:41:08,122
We got ditched by our peer mentors

919
00:41:08,430 --> 00:41:10,586
so we came to get something to eat
before going back to our dorm.

920
00:41:10,811 --> 00:41:12,365
That’s so sad.

921
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,573
Come.

922
00:41:14,927 --> 00:41:15,521
Sit with us.

923
00:41:15,554 --> 00:41:16,327
It’s Arc’s treat.

924
00:41:16,346 --> 00:41:17,288
We don’t want to trouble him.

925
00:41:18,232 --> 00:41:19,152
You should be worried about troubling me.

926
00:41:19,401 --> 00:41:21,920
I’ve strained my neck from
looking up to talk to you. Come.

927
00:41:22,223 --> 00:41:23,077
Have a seat, Gun.

928
00:41:23,542 --> 00:41:24,028
Come on.

929
00:41:27,226 --> 00:41:29,794
Faifa, you’re in Electrical Engineering, right?

930
00:41:30,174 --> 00:41:30,645
Yes.

931
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:32,408
What about you, Gun?

932
00:41:33,502 --> 00:41:34,469
Chemical Engineering.

933
00:41:35,011 --> 00:41:37,700
Wow. Chemical Engineering is tough.

934
00:41:38,136 --> 00:41:40,065
You’re impressive for getting in.

935
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:43,533
Thank you.

936
00:41:45,288 --> 00:41:46,737
When you interviewed,

937
00:41:47,465 --> 00:41:49,398
did the professors ask you any weird questions?

938
00:41:49,774 --> 00:41:50,469
Only normal ones.

939
00:41:50,869 --> 00:41:52,469
Same for me.

940
00:41:52,653 --> 00:41:53,157
Really?

941
00:41:54,979 --> 00:41:56,100
See? I told you.

942
00:41:56,420 --> 00:41:58,002
No one was asked anything weird like you were,

943
00:41:58,346 --> 00:41:59,573
Anon, the debt-free.

944
00:42:00,490 --> 00:42:01,720
It’s “the person who has no debt.”

945
00:42:01,810 --> 00:42:03,720
You never get it right.
Don’t make me kiss you on the lips.

946
00:42:04,561 --> 00:42:05,402
You may not have debts,

947
00:42:05,788 --> 00:42:06,499
but you have me.

948
00:42:08,684 --> 00:42:09,962
What an old joke.

949
00:42:11,157 --> 00:42:11,848
But I love it.

950
00:42:11,860 --> 00:42:12,706
Keep it coming.

951
00:42:14,611 --> 00:42:16,598
Are you Anon, the debt-free?

952
00:42:17,139 --> 00:42:18,500
Yes, why?

953
00:42:18,564 --> 00:42:19,811
You’ve heard of it before?

954
00:42:26,637 --> 00:42:27,625
Stop patting too much

955
00:42:27,641 --> 00:42:28,337
or I’ll throw up.

956
00:42:28,451 --> 00:42:29,240
Come on.

957
00:42:29,325 --> 00:42:29,952
It’ll be over soon

958
00:42:31,034 --> 00:42:31,899
You’re not one to talk.

959
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:34,109
You’re done but your legs are still shaking.

960
00:42:36,690 --> 00:42:37,500
They’re not shaking.

961
00:42:38,656 --> 00:42:40,234
Last applicant for Chemical Engineering.

962
00:42:40,311 --> 00:42:42,217
Mr. Gunyukhol Jiraroj, please come in.

963
00:42:43,411 --> 00:42:43,965
Listen.

964
00:42:44,740 --> 00:42:45,576
You can do it.

965
00:42:50,468 --> 00:42:51,266
- I got this!
- You got this!

966
00:42:51,773 --> 00:42:52,620
I can do it!

967
00:42:58,918 --> 00:42:59,509
Hello.

968
00:43:00,749 --> 00:43:03,408
Please introduce yourself.

969
00:43:05,934 --> 00:43:07,072
Hello again.

970
00:43:07,441 --> 00:43:09,047
I’m Gunyukhol Jiraroj.

971
00:43:14,988 --> 00:43:15,699
Uh…

972
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:17,887
My nickname is Gun,

973
00:43:18,244 --> 00:43:20,105
which is short for my first name.

974
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:23,511
And just in case you don’t know,

975
00:43:24,727 --> 00:43:26,251
Gunyukhol means two ears.

976
00:43:29,690 --> 00:43:33,048
The professors said there was someone
with an unusual name like mine last year.

977
00:43:33,391 --> 00:43:34,888
Wow.

978
00:43:35,911 --> 00:43:37,940
We really are the legends of engineering.

979
00:43:38,388 --> 00:43:40,198
Nice to meet you, Junior.

980
00:43:41,631 --> 00:43:42,888
Nice to meet you too, Senior.

981
00:43:46,739 --> 00:43:47,490
Let’s eat.

982
00:43:47,909 --> 00:43:49,324
Can we get two more rice?

983
00:44:18,743 --> 00:44:19,201
Oh.

984
00:44:20,244 --> 00:44:21,232
His bag is here.

985
00:44:23,659 --> 00:44:24,211
Hello?

986
00:44:24,825 --> 00:44:25,480
Where are you?

987
00:44:25,671 --> 00:44:27,202
(I’m waiting for my senior’s lecture notes,)

988
00:44:27,420 --> 00:44:28,041
(then I’ll head up.)

989
00:44:28,432 --> 00:44:29,045
Okay.

990
00:44:31,894 --> 00:44:32,736
I’m going to take a shower.

991
00:44:45,841 --> 00:44:46,494
I’m sleepy.

992
00:44:48,811 --> 00:44:49,293
Hey.

993
00:44:50,207 --> 00:44:51,037
Are you going to the bar?

994
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:52,240
Yeah.

995
00:44:52,496 --> 00:44:54,388
Are you sleeping here tonight or at the bar?

996
00:44:55,102 --> 00:44:55,896
Probably the bar.

997
00:44:57,431 --> 00:44:58,410
Call me if you need anything.

998
00:45:10,965 --> 00:45:11,448
Hey.

999
00:45:11,671 --> 00:45:12,170
Hmm?

1000
00:45:13,340 --> 00:45:15,071
Can I see what’s inside the box?

1001
00:45:15,434 --> 00:45:15,957
Sure.

1002
00:45:27,194 --> 00:45:28,103
So cute.

1003
00:45:33,069 --> 00:45:34,700
When you sleep here, can you wear these?

1004
00:45:37,022 --> 00:45:38,324
Today I drew lots to get into
a peer mentoring group

1005
00:45:38,611 --> 00:45:40,170
and then went out to eat with my friends.

1006
00:45:40,551 --> 00:45:42,714
As soon as I got out of the shower, I called you.

1007
00:45:43,170 --> 00:45:44,952
(Have you made new friends?)

1008
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:47,748
I’ll probably get to know
new people in the core classes.

1009
00:45:48,216 --> 00:45:49,361
But right now, I only know Kong

1010
00:45:49,380 --> 00:45:51,297
and our new friend Faifa.

1011
00:45:51,936 --> 00:45:53,297
(Only one new friend?)

1012
00:45:54,120 --> 00:45:57,271
Actually, there’s one more named Yotha.

1013
00:46:03,598 --> 00:46:04,702
(Is something wrong?)

1014
00:46:06,405 --> 00:46:07,783
No, Mom.

1015
00:46:08,376 --> 00:46:10,475
I’m just sleepy.

1016
00:46:12,103 --> 00:46:13,451
(Then sleep.)

1017
00:46:13,725 --> 00:46:14,823
(Let’s talk tomorrow.)

1018
00:46:15,032 --> 00:46:16,157
(I love you, son.)

1019
00:46:16,382 --> 00:46:17,176
I love you too, Mom.

1020
00:46:43,195 --> 00:46:44,395
The power on our floor went out.

1021
00:46:44,758 --> 00:46:45,398
I know.

1022
00:46:45,771 --> 00:46:46,718
It’ll be back at 5 a.m. tomorrow.

1023
00:46:47,222 --> 00:46:48,032
Did they announce that?

1024
00:46:48,232 --> 00:46:49,674
Yes, in the group chat.

1025
00:46:50,960 --> 00:46:52,600
You should start paying
attention to these things.

1026
00:46:53,877 --> 00:46:55,896
You pay too much attention to everything.

1027
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:57,228
Come in.

1028
00:47:00,084 --> 00:47:01,179
What’s going on?

1029
00:47:03,431 --> 00:47:04,745
Gun can’t sleep without the lights on,

1030
00:47:04,927 --> 00:47:07,120
so I’m leaving him here.

1031
00:47:08,441 --> 00:47:10,028
Why can’t you sleep without the lights on?

1032
00:47:11,588 --> 00:47:12,814
It’s a long story.

1033
00:47:14,389 --> 00:47:16,522
But if you can’t sleep with the lights on, it’s okay.

1034
00:47:16,914 --> 00:47:17,611
I’ll go…

1035
00:47:17,631 --> 00:47:18,250
It’s fine.

1036
00:47:18,820 --> 00:47:20,214
Yotha is not coming back tonight.

1037
00:47:20,256 --> 00:47:21,111
You can sleep in his bed.

1038
00:47:21,554 --> 00:47:22,635
What about you, Kong?

1039
00:47:22,945 --> 00:47:24,435
It’s hot. Do you want to sleep here with us?

1040
00:47:24,454 --> 00:47:25,256
No, I’ll be fine.

1041
00:47:25,472 --> 00:47:26,546
I have a celebrity portable fan.

1042
00:47:27,112 --> 00:47:27,617
Here.

1043
00:47:30,983 --> 00:47:31,703
How’s that?

1044
00:47:31,764 --> 00:47:32,472
Cold, right?

1045
00:47:33,804 --> 00:47:36,265
Please take care of him.

1046
00:47:37,170 --> 00:47:37,608
See you.

1047
00:47:37,669 --> 00:47:38,186
Okay.

1048
00:47:38,804 --> 00:47:39,328
Bye.

1049
00:47:39,394 --> 00:47:39,927
Bye.

1050
00:47:42,668 --> 00:47:43,743
Make yourself at home.

1051
00:47:44,875 --> 00:47:46,925
Why isn’t Yotha coming back to the dorm?

1052
00:47:47,411 --> 00:47:48,207
Don’t they check attendance?

1053
00:47:49,256 --> 00:47:50,757
He doesn’t care about these things.

1054
00:47:52,084 --> 00:47:52,853
Where is he?

1055
00:47:53,065 --> 00:47:53,613
Did he go home?

1056
00:47:55,392 --> 00:47:56,826
His story is as long as yours

1057
00:47:56,845 --> 00:47:58,921
about not being able to
sleep without the lights on.

1058
00:48:00,070 --> 00:48:01,478
Just forget it.

1059
00:48:02,071 --> 00:48:02,666
Let’s sleep.

1060
00:48:06,782 --> 00:48:07,765
I’ll sleep on the floor.

1061
00:48:08,016 --> 00:48:09,177
I don’t want to trouble Yotha.

1062
00:48:09,238 --> 00:48:10,672
Don’t worry about him.

1063
00:48:10,693 --> 00:48:11,912
He’s not coming back tonight.

1064
00:48:12,219 --> 00:48:14,457
So, should I keep all the lights on

1065
00:48:14,472 --> 00:48:15,893
or can I leave just the lamps on?

1066
00:48:18,586 --> 00:48:19,508
Just the lamps are enough.

1067
00:48:19,850 --> 00:48:20,457
Are you sure?

1068
00:48:20,517 --> 00:48:20,973
Yeah.

1069
00:48:20,989 --> 00:48:21,520
Okay.

1070
00:48:22,035 --> 00:48:22,857
Thank you.

1071
00:48:27,703 --> 00:48:28,453
You’re okay, right?

1072
00:48:29,634 --> 00:48:30,222
Yes.

1073
00:48:30,653 --> 00:48:31,194
I’m okay.

1074
00:48:31,842 --> 00:48:32,718
Make yourself at home.

1075
00:48:32,734 --> 00:48:33,395
Good night.

1076
00:48:33,680 --> 00:48:34,474
I should sleep.

1077
00:48:40,431 --> 00:48:42,160
May I, Mr. Darkness?

1078
00:48:53,662 --> 00:48:54,373
Just sleep, Gun.

1079
00:49:45,954 --> 00:49:46,454
Hey.

1080
00:49:48,142 --> 00:49:48,651
Hey.

1081
00:49:52,915 --> 00:49:53,365
Gun.

1082
00:49:54,869 --> 00:49:55,376
Gun.

1083
00:50:01,260 --> 00:50:01,768
Gun.

1084
00:50:03,330 --> 00:50:03,817
Gun.

1085
00:50:04,761 --> 00:50:05,315
Gun, wake up.

1086
00:50:08,038 --> 00:50:08,521
Gun.

1087
00:50:21,943 --> 00:50:23,282
Hi, new roommate.

1088
00:50:23,711 --> 00:50:24,760
Let me tie it for you.

1089
00:50:26,736 --> 00:50:27,315
Nuisance.

1090
00:50:28,277 --> 00:50:29,601
Don’t tell me you like this kind of thing.

1091
00:50:31,573 --> 00:50:32,231
Meddler.

1092
00:50:33,854 --> 00:50:34,933
Is something going on, Arc?

1093
00:50:36,977 --> 00:50:38,367
Let me hug you tightly before I tell you.

1094
00:50:38,619 --> 00:50:39,202
Tie it for me.

1095
00:50:39,557 --> 00:50:40,801
When you think of Engineering,

1096
00:50:41,037 --> 00:50:42,308
what’s the first thing that comes to mind?

1097
00:50:42,521 --> 00:50:43,060
You.

1098
00:50:45,481 --> 00:50:46,348
The number one

1099
00:50:47,047 --> 00:50:48,875
troublemaker in Engineering.

